🔹 Remove Nth Node From End of List

🧠 Problem Statement
Given the head of a singly linked list, remove the nth node from the end and return the updated head.

🔹 Idea of Your Approach
👉 First pass → count total nodes
👉 Second pass → delete (count - n)th node from start

Code Explanation (Line by Line)
🔸 Step 1: Handle empty list
if(head==NULL){
    return NULL; 
}

👉 If list is empty → nothing to delete

🔸 Step 2: Count total nodes
ListNode* curr=head;
int count=0;
while(curr!=NULL){
    count++;
    curr=curr->next;
}

👉 Traverse full list and count nodes

Example:

1 → 2 → 3 → 4 → 5
count = 5
🔸 Step 3: Special case (delete head)
if(count==n){
    ListNode* temp=head;
    head=head->next;
    delete(temp);
    return head;
}

👉 If n == count
→ means delete 1st node from start (head)

Example:

[1,2,3], n=3 → delete 1

✔️ Update head
✔️ Free memory

🔸 Step 4: Find target position
int target=count-n;

👉 Convert:

Nth from end → (count - n)th from start

Example:

count = 5, n = 2
target = 5 - 2 = 3

👉 We need to reach node before deletion point

🔸 Step 5: Move to (target-1) node
curr=head;
for(int i=1;i<target;i++){
    curr=curr->next;
}

👉 Move curr to node just before the one to delete
Example:

1 → 2 → 3 → 4 → 5
            ↑ delete 4

curr stops at 3
🔸 Step 6: Delete node
ListNode* temp=curr->next;
curr->next=curr->next->next;
delete(temp);

👉 Standard deletion in linked list:

Before:

3 → 4 → 5

After:

3 → 5
🔸 Step 7: Return head
return head;
🔁 Full Dry Run
Input:
1 → 2 → 3 → 4 → 5, n = 2
Step 1: Count
count = 5
Step 2: target
target = 5 - 2 = 3
Step 3: Move curr
curr → 3
Step 4: Delete
curr->next = 4 → remove it
Final Output:
1 → 2 → 3 → 5
⚡ Complexity
Time: O(n) + O(n) = O(n)
Space: O(1)
🔥 Important Observations
✅ Why i < target?

Because:

We want node before deletion
Not the node to delete
✅ Why special case needed?

Because:

Deleting head → no previous node exists
🚀 Comparison with Optimal (One-pass)
Approach	Passes	Difficulty
Your code	2-pass	Easy 👍
Two pointer	1-pass	Optimal 🚀
🔥 Summary

👉 First count nodes
👉 Convert position
👉 Traverse again
👉 Delete node

Code implementation:
class Solution {
public:
    ListNode* removeNthFromEnd(ListNode* head, int n) {
        if(head==NULL){
            return NULL; 
        }
        ListNode* curr=head;
        int count=0;
        while(curr!=NULL){
            count++;
            curr=curr->next;
        }
        if(count==n){
            ListNode* temp=head;
            head=head->next;
            delete(temp);
            return head;
        }
        int target=count-n;
        curr=head;
        for(int i=1;i<target;i++){
            curr=curr->next;
        }

            ListNode* temp=curr->next;
            curr->next=curr->next->next;
            delete(temp);
        
        return head;
    }
};
